80779>
80779>        Use Dd_debug.dg // This Provides access to dd debugger by pressing ctrl+d within any view. Good for debugging
Including file: Dd_debug.dg    (C:\Program Files (x86)\DataFlex 19.0\Pkg\Dd_debug.dg)
80779>>>// dd_debug.dg - DDO debugger/inspector
80779>>>//
80779>>>// Copyright Data Access WorldWide 2003
80779>>>// John Tuohy
80779>>>//
80779>>>// By adding this to any Windows view or application (with a "use DD_Debug.dg") you can
80779>>>// inspect your DDOs and make sure they are doing what you think. To invoke this panel you
80779>>>// need to press ctrl/d (or send DebugDDs).
80779>>>//
80779>>>// As of 9.1, this also tests for sending reentrant messages to the DDO when the DDO is busy.
80779>>>// Normally, these messages are ignored - now you get an error message (so you can fix it).
80779>>>// Also, you can set a limit for number of filtered records so you can see if you are using
80779>>>// optimized and non-optimized indexes the way you think you are.
80779>>>//
80779>>>// NOTE: This package should NEVER appear in a deployed application. It is just for your
80779>>>//       own development and testing.
80779>>>
80779>>>
80779>>>
80779>>>Validate_Packages 18 0 1
80779>>>
80779>>>Define CR_LF for (Character(13)+Character(10))
80779>>>
80779>>>// This provides support for DDO Rentancy checking and for testing for
80779>>>// non-optimal finding.
80779>>>Use DD_OperationChecker.pkg
Including file: dd_OperationChecker.pkg    (C:\Program Files (x86)\DataFlex 19.0\Pkg\dd_OperationChecker.pkg)
80779>>>>>// dd_OperationChecker.pkg for VDF10.0
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// Copyright Data Access WorldWide 2003
80779>>>>>// John Tuohy
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// One of the harder DDO errors to see is the issue of reentrancy. A number of the DDO operations are not
80779>>>>>// reentrant. When a message such as Request_Save, Request_find or Clear is sent to a DDO all DDOs are considered
80779>>>>>// to be "busy" until the operationis complete. While DDOs are busy you can not send messages to ANY other DDO in
80779>>>>>// ANY other part of your application. The file structure of DDOs and the the C structure of DDOs do not allow this.
80779>>>>>// If you do send a reentrant message while the DDOs are busy the reentrant message is ignored. Here lies the problem.
80779>>>>>// You are trying to perform some kind of DDO customization and some of these customized behaviors are ignored without
80779>>>>>// any kind of warning or error.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// The following DDO messages are non re-entrant. While any of these methods are being processed you cannot send any of these
80779>>>>>// messages to any DDOs.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>//     Clear
80779>>>>>//     Clear_All
80779>>>>>//     Request_save
80779>>>>>//     Request_delete
80779>>>>>//     Request_assign
80779>>>>>//     Request_find
80779>>>>>//     Request_Superfind
80779>>>>>//     Find_by_recnum
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// This package provides diagnostic code that checks these messages and makes sure that are not trying to call them in a busy state.
80779>>>>>// Instead of the busy operation being ignored, an error will be reported. Once you see the error, you can fix it.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// In addition, there is a check built in here for non-optimal finding operations. You can set the value of giNonOptimalFindCount
80779>>>>>// to a non zero value and when a find operation filters that many recods, you will get an error.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// IMPORTANT: This is a debug package and should never be used in deployed applications. It should be used by the developer
80779>>>>>// to test their application. Once tested, the code should be removed.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// To Use
80779>>>>>// ------
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// This is used as part of DD_Debug.dg. While this could be used stand-alone you really don't want to do this.
80779>>>>>//
80779>>>>>// NOTE: This can only be used with VDF9.1 or above. If you try to use this with older packages this will not compile!
80779>>>>>
80779>>>>>Validate_Packages 9 1 0
80779>>>>>Use Data_set.pkg
80779>>>>>
80779>>>>>// This variable determines of the rentrancy tests should be performed. dd_debug will use and set this
80779>>>>>Global_variable Integer gbTestRentrancy
80779>>>>>Move 1 to gbTestRentrancy
80780>>>>>
80780>>>>>// This determines how many failed finds is considered to be non-optimal. When 0, there is no check.
80780>>>>>Global_variable Integer giNonOptimalFindCount
80780>>>>>Move 0 to giNonOptimalFindCount
80781>>>>>
80781>>>>>Procedure CheckRentrancy for DataSet handle hoDD string sMessage
80783>>>>>    String sMess sVal
80783>>>>>    
80783>>>>>    If (gbTestRentrancy=0 or operation_mode=mode_waiting) Procedure_Return
80786>>>>>    
80786>>>>>    If (OPERATION_MODE=MODE_VALIDATING and Lowercase(sMessage)<>"request_save") Begin
80788>>>>>        // mode_validating is not really a non-reentrant DD function from the runtime's point of view. The DDs
80788>>>>>        // keep track of this mode. Therefore, we will let a re-entrant DD message pass through for all cases, except
80788>>>>>        // request_save because trying to perform a save while inside of a validate is most likely wrong.
80788>>>>>        Procedure_Return
80789>>>>>    End
80789>>>>>>
80789>>>>>    
80789>>>>>    Move ("DDO re-entrant operation attempted.\n\n"+;          "Message = " - sMessage - ".  Object =" - name(hoDD) -".\n"+ ;          "\nCurrent Operation_mode is " + string(operation_mode) +;          "\nCurrent Operation_origin is " + string(operation_origin) * name(operation_origin) ) to sMess
80790>>>>>    Error DFERR_PROGRAM sMess
80791>>>>>>
80791>>>>>end_procedure
80792>>>>>
80792>>>>>Procedure NonOptimalTest for DataSet  Handle hoDD string sMessage integer iOldDif integer iFile integer iIndex
80794>>>>>    string sMess
80794>>>>>    Integer iNewDif
80794>>>>>
80794>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iNewDif
80795>>>>>    If (iNewDif-iOldDif>giNonOptimalFindCount) Begin
80797>>>>>        Move ("Constrained Find may not be Optimized.\n\n"+;              "Message =" - sMessage - ".  Object = " - name(hoDD) -".\n"+ ;              "Test finds exceeds the limit of" * string(giNonOptimalFindCount) * "filtered records.\n" +;              "Number of records searched = " + string(iNewDif-iOldDif) + ".") to sMess
80798>>>>>        If (iFile>0) Begin
80800>>>>>            // if iFile is zero we don't don't which file is being found (i.e. Locate_next)
80800>>>>>            Move (sMess + "\nFile = " + string(iFile) + ". Index = "+ string(iIndex) + ".") to sMess
80801>>>>>        End
80801>>>>>>
80801>>>>>        Error DFERR_PROGRAM sMess
80802>>>>>>
80802>>>>>    end
80802>>>>>>
80802>>>>>end_procedure
80803>>>>>
80803>>>>>
80803>>>>>Procedure Clear for DataSet
80805>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "clear"
80806>>>>>    forward send clear
80808>>>>>end_procedure
80809>>>>>
80809>>>>>Procedure Clear_All for DataSet
80811>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "clear_all"
80812>>>>>    forward send clear_all
80814>>>>>end_procedure
80815>>>>>
80815>>>>>Procedure Request_Save for DataSet
80817>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_save"
80818>>>>>    forward send request_save
80820>>>>>end_procedure
80821>>>>>
80821>>>>>Procedure Request_Delete for DataSet
80823>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_delete"
80824>>>>>    forward send request_delete
80826>>>>>end_procedure
80827>>>>>
80827>>>>>Procedure Request_Assign for DataSet integer iFile
80829>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_assign"
80830>>>>>    If (num_arguments=0) ;        forward send request_assign
80834>>>>>    else ;        forward send request_assign iFile
80837>>>>>end_procedure
80838>>>>>
80838>>>>>Procedure Find_By_Recnum for DataSet integer iFile integer iRecord
80840>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "Find_by_recnum"
80841>>>>>    forward send Find_by_recnum iFile iRecord
80843>>>>>end_procedure
80844>>>>>
80844>>>>>Procedure Request_Find for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iIndex
80846>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80846>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_find"
80847>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80848>>>>>    forward send request_find iMode iFile iIndex
80850>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80852>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest self "request_find" iOldDif iFile iIndex
80853>>>>>    End
80853>>>>>>
80853>>>>>end_procedure
80854>>>>>
80854>>>>>Procedure Request_Read for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iIndex
80856>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80856>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80857>>>>>    forward send request_Read iMode iFile iIndex
80859>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80861>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest  self "request_read" iOldDif iFile iIndex
80862>>>>>    End
80862>>>>>>
80862>>>>>end_procedure
80863>>>>>
80863>>>>>
80863>>>>>Procedure Request_Superfind for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iField
80865>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80865>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_Superfind"
80866>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80867>>>>>    forward send Request_Superfind iMode iFile iField
80869>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80871>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest  self "request_Superfind" iOldDif 0 0 // we don't have a file or an index
80872>>>>>    End
80872>>>>>>
80872>>>>>end_procedure
80873>>>>>
80873>>>
