82120>>>
82120>>>// This provides a quick and simple way to create an about package for a program.
82120>>>// You need to create a message inside you client area called Activate_About.
82120>>>// Within this message you should send the message DoAbout passing needed
82120>>>// string information.
82120>>>//
82120>>>//       Procedure Activate_About
82120>>>//           Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor sBitmap
82120>>>//       End_Procedure
82120>>>//    where: sTitle =     Name of application. If none provided, uses caption
82120>>>//                        bar title
82120>>>//           sVersion   = Version Line. If none provided, will be blank
82120>>>//           sCopyRight = Copyright Line. If none provided, will be blank
82120>>>//           sAuthor    = Author name, blank if none provided
82120>>>//           sBitMap    = Bitmap logo. If none provided, standard VDF bitmap
82120>>>//                        is used.
82120>>>// It is expected that you will place this in your own object package. For
82120>>>// example an order about package may look like this:
82120>>>//
82120>>>//   // OrderAbout.pkg
82120>>>//   Use StdAbout.pkg
82120>>>//   Procedure Activate_About
82120>>>//      String sTitle sCopyright sVersion sAuthor
82120>>>//      Move "My Order Entry System" to sTitle
82120>>>//      Move "Version 2.1" to sVersion
82120>>>//      Move "Copyright 1997, Super Software Inc." to sCopyright
82120>>>//      Move "John Smith"  to sAuthor
82120>>>//      Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor ""
82120>>>//   end_procedure
82120>>>//   // end of file.
82120>>>
82120>>>Use DfAbout.pkg
Including file: DfAbout.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\DfAbout.pkg)
82120>>>>>//************************************************************************
