83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_SET_MODE
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Allows switching between set-oriented and record oriented fetch modes.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is set to True, the driver will fetch a set of records
83027>>>>>>>/// for each find. If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is False, the driver will fetch only one
83027>>>>>>>/// record at a time. This attribute can also be specified in the .INT file during
83027>>>>>>>/// migration through Flex2SQL. This settings is normally used alongside
83027>>>>>>>/// DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS to set the number of rows to return and DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83027>>>>>>>/// to turn on local caching.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Note: Turning off set-mode can have a detrimental impact on performance. Unless
83027>>>>>>>/// there is a specific reason to do otherwise, this option should be left on.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Default value: True
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83027>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT OPTIMIZE {FOR_SET | ONE_ROW}
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Mode for the FileNumber. True for set-mode, False for one-row mode.
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83027>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to True
83027>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to boolVar
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_SET_MODE                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+5)
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_DATABASENAME
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string containing the name of the database where the
83027>>>>>>>/// table referenced by the passed File Number resides. This is a READ ONLY
83027>>>>>>>/// attribute. Note that because Oracle doesn't support the concept of multiple
83027>>>>>>>/// databases on one server, this attribute is not valid for Oracle.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex, MySQLFlex, PGFlex
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83027>>>>>>>/// @See
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Name of the Database
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83027>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of Orderhea.File_Number to strVal
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_DATABASENAME                         For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+6)
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Controls the maximum number of rows retrieved by a Find GT/LT
83027>>>>>>>/// operation. The driver will automatically retrieve and cache this many rows
83027>>>>>>>/// for future find GT/LT operations. Setting this property to a very high
83027>>>>>>>/// value can be inefficient from a UI perspective but may be advisable for
83027>>>>>>>/// local processing of rows (such as in a batch process).
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Default value: 10
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83027>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_SET_MODE DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT MAX_ROWS_TO_QUERY {integer}
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Attribute Value
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83027>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to 10
83027>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to intVal
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+7)
83027>>>>>>>
