83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description When creating records on a table with RECNUM support, the
83027>>>>>>>/// record number is returned after creation. When this attribute is false, the newly
83027>>>>>>>/// created record's RECNUM is not returned from the server. This could result in a
83027>>>>>>>/// slight performance improvement when many records are being created in a loop.
83027>>>>>>>/// The optimization, however, is negligible.  Having this attribute set to false can
83027>>>>>>>/// have detrimental effects if used improperly; i.e. DD-based saves or UI-based
83027>>>>>>>/// operations. Thus, this should almost always be set to true unless there is a
83027>>>>>>>/// compelling reason to do otherwise.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Default Value: True
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-31 by Aaron Gulack
83027>>>>>>>/// @See
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable. false to not retrieve record number, true otherwise.
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// open ORDERHEA
83027>>>>>>>/// Handle  hFile
83027>>>>>>>/// Boolean bRetrieve
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of hFile to false
83027>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of hFile To bRetrieve
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM                      For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+17)
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_NAME_SPACE
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description In Postgres, schemas are objects where all the tables,views and indexes
83027>>>>>>>/// are stored. Separate schemas are used to specify relational data. This attribute is
83027>>>>>>>/// used to set the name of the schema where a table is created. Schema's do not account
83027>>>>>>>/// for any physical space but are merely used as theory to explain the order of a database.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     PGFlex
