83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_GET_SERVERNAME_FROM_LOGIN
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this attribute to specify whether the SERVER_NAME option will
83027>>>>>>>/// be included in the INT file.  If set to True, the SERVER_NAME option will not
83027>>>>>>>/// be included in the INT file, if set to false, the SERVER_NAME option will be
83027>>>>>>>/// included in the INT file. This has two uses. The first is during a Structure_Start
83027>>>>>>>/// i.e. table creation/modification. The other is when using the OUTPUT_INT_FILE
83027>>>>>>>/// command. Set this attribute before the OUTPUT_INT_FILE to indicate how the INT
83027>>>>>>>/// file will be written. This name indicates a backwards logic so take note that
83027>>>>>>>/// setting it to true will NOT include the SERVER_NAME in the INT file.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Default Value: False
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-01 by Aaron Gulack
