83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Table locking is done during transactions to maintain atomicity.
83027>>>>>>>/// In DataFlex, this is usually done with the REREAD/UNLOCK commands. This
83027>>>>>>>/// attribute is used to get the status of a table lock. If a table is currently
83027>>>>>>>/// in a REREAD, or locked, then the attribute will return true. Otherwise, it
83027>>>>>>>/// returns false. It is a read-only attribute so no setting can be done.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-06 by Aaron Gulack
83027>>>>>>>/// @See
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Indicates the status of the file lock
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// open Customer
83027>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
83027>>>>>>>/// Integer bLocked
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS of hFile to bLocked
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_LOCK_RECORD_STATUS                   For 632
83027>>>>>>>
