83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FIELD_TIME_ON
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Assign a field to retrieve Time Stamp value from a DATETIME
83027>>>>>>>/// column in a table.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// This option was implemented because some versions of DataFlex do not support
83027>>>>>>>/// DATETIME fields normally supported by SQL databases.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// To use this: Change the type of a date field in your FD to string type,
83027>>>>>>>/// Set the attribute DF_FIELD_TIME_ON of this field to TRUE and
83027>>>>>>>/// recompile your program.
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote
83027>>>>>>>/// @See
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_TIME_ON of <FileNumber|FileName FieldNumber> to DFTRUE | DFFALSE
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileName              Name of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldNumber           Number of the field
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// #INCLUDE MERTECH.INC
83027>>>>>>>/// string sDateTime sDatabaseName
83027>>>>>>>/// open ORDERHEA
83027>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FIELD_TIME_ON of 30 3 to dfTrue
83027>>>>>>>/// find GE ORDERHEA by recnum
83027>>>>>>>/// move ORDERHEA.ORDER_DATE to sDateTime
83027>>>>>>>/// showln "sDateTime: " sDateTime
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FIELD_TIME_ON                             For (DF_FIELD_NATIVE_LENGTH+8)
83027>>>>>>>
