83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_INDEX_STATUS
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Oracle has an attribute for indexes called "STATUS" which indicates
83027>>>>>>>/// whether or not an index is valid for use. This attribute can only be used to get
83027>>>>>>>/// the value of the "STATUS" property in Oracle. It currently does not support setting
83027>>>>>>>/// the attribute. The two values for this attribute are "VALID" or "UNUSABLE".
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// This is a ReadOnly attribute
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
