83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_INDEX_UNIQUE
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description An index on a column that is unique is considered so if it
83027>>>>>>>/// does not have two equal values in that column in two different rows. This
83027>>>>>>>/// attribute is used to find out whether or not the specified index is unique.
83027>>>>>>>/// If it is, this attribute will return "U" indicating that it is indeed unique.
83027>>>>>>>/// This is important to note because when getting the value of this attribute,
83027>>>>>>>/// a string variable must be used. Since this is a ReadOnly attribute, setting
83027>>>>>>>/// an idex to unique cannot be done with this attribute.
