83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description Dataflex's embedded database, by default, uses a Recnum column
83027>>>>>>>/// as the unique identifier for a table instead of a primary key. A table can
83027>>>>>>>/// easily be changed to use another column though and this attribute gets or
83027>>>>>>>/// sets whether the Recnum is being used for a table. Getting the value of this
83027>>>>>>>/// attribute can be done at any time for any driver. The setting of this attribute,
83027>>>>>>>/// however, can only be done in certain situations. Only if an alternative primary
83027>>>>>>>/// key is set up already can this attribute be set to false and only during a
83027>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start. Also, the attribute can only be turned off (set to false),
83027>>>>>>>/// it can not be turned back on (set to True).
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Note: In Postgres, this attribute is a ReadOnly attribute and can not be set.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public (PGFlex ReadOnly)
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-12 by Aaron Gulack
83027>>>>>>>/// @See                 DF_FILE_RECNUM_NAME DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable indicating if recnum is used
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Boolean bRecnum
83027>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
83027>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of Customer.File_Number to False
83027>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of Customer.File_Number to bRecnum
83027>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE                         For 1401
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83027>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX
83027>>>>>>>/// @Description This attribute gets or sets the index which is used as the
83027>>>>>>>/// primary key for a table. The variable used for this attribute is an integer
83027>>>>>>>/// containing the numbered index used. Getting the value of this attribute can
83027>>>>>>>/// be done at any time, whereas setting can only be done at table creation or
83027>>>>>>>/// during a Structure_Start. If a RECNUM is used as the unique identifier then
83027>>>>>>>/// 0 is returned.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Note: In Postgres this attribute is ReadOnly, so it can only be used to get
83027>>>>>>>/// the index used as the primary key.
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83027>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public (PGFlex ReadOnly)
83027>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83027>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-12 by Aaron Gulack
83027>>>>>>>/// @See                 DF_FILE_RECNUM_NAME
83027>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83027>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable indicating if a primary key is used
83027>>>>>>>/// @Example
83027>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Boolean bPrimary
83027>>>>>>>/// Handle hFile
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Move Customer.File_Number to hFile
83027>>>>>>>///
83027>>>>>>>/// Structure_Start hFile
83027>>>>>>>///     Set_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of Customer.File_Number to False
83027>>>>>>>///     Get_Attribute DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX of Customer.File_Number to bPrimary
83027>>>>>>>/// Structure_End hFile
83027>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_PRIMARY_INDEX                        For 1402
83027>>>>>>>
83027>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
