83029>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83029>>>>>>>//Comment Block Template
83029>>>>>>>//======================
83029>>>>>>>
83029>>>>>>>/// @Name {Name of the command for indexing} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>/// @Description {Short Command Description} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>///     The description can be multiple lines, and contain HTML tags.
83029>>>>>>>///     The other tokens will have HTML encoded so we can show stuff
83029>>>>>>>///     like <param1> properly. A blank line will automatically be
83029>>>>>>>///         translated into a paragraph break in the documentation, so
83029>>>>>>>///     no need for <br> or <p> tags.
83029>>>>>>>///
83029>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions {Assumptions made in order for the command to work}
83029>>>>>>>/// @Status {Obsolete, Internal, or Public} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>/// @Drivers {DB2Flex, MySQLFlex, ORAFlex, PgFlex, SQLFlex or All} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote {Date and author of the last revision}
83029>>>>>>>/// @See {list of related commands}
83029>>>>>>>///
83029>>>>>>>/// @Syntax {Syntax of use} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>/// @Param {Each parameter with a brief description} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>/// @DBMS {List of supported databases}
83029>>>>>>>/// @DataFlex {List of supported DataFlex versions}
83029>>>>>>>/// @Usage {Different uses command can have multiple syntaxes} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>///
83029>>>>>>>/// @Example {An example of the command being used} (used for documentation)
83029>>>>>>>
83029>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83029>>>>>>>/// @Name        DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME
83029>>>>>>>/// @Description Retrieves the current driver name and or the file number
83029>>>>>>>/// that will be used by the macro commands.
83029>>>>>>>///
83029>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83029>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal Use Only
83029>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83029>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-07-14 By Ian Smith
83029>>>>>>>/// @See
83029>>>>>>>
83029>>>>>>>//Most commands use DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME so this code was being duplicated
83029>>>>>>>//all the time. It has been moved to this method to remove that duplication.
83029>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_Get_Driver_name Global
83031>>>>>>>    //If we have a file number get its driver, else find first loaded Mertech driver
83031>>>>>>>    If MertechInc_FileNumber GT 0 ;        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DRIVER of MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_DriverName
83036>>>>>>>    Else Begin
83037>>>>>>>        If (MertechInc_CurrentDriver > "") Move MertechInc_CurrentDriver to MertechInc_DriverName
83040>>>>>>>        Else Begin
83041>>>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_NUMBER_DRIVERS to MertechInc_iCount
83044>>>>>>>            For MertechInc_iLoop from 1 to MertechInc_iCount
83050>>>>>>>>
83050>>>>>>>                Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_NAME of MertechInc_iLoop to MertechInc_DriverName
83053>>>>>>>                Move (UPPERCASE(MertechInc_DriverName)) to MertechInc_DriverName
83054>>>>>>>                If (MertechInc_DriverName EQ ORAFLEX  or MertechInc_DriverName EQ SQLFLEX or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSDB2 or ;                    MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSPgSQL or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSMySQL) Move MertechInc_iCount to MertechInc_iLoop
83057>>>>>>>                Else Move "" to MertechInc_DriverName
83059>>>>>>>            Loop
83060>>>>>>>>
83060>>>>>>>        End
83060>>>>>>>>
83060>>>>>>>    End
83060>>>>>>>>
83060>>>>>>>
83060>>>>>>>    //Ensure that we return a valid Mertech driver.
83060>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_DriverName NE ORAFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE SQLFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSDB2   and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSPgSQL and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSMySQL     ) ;        Begin
83062>>>>>>>
83062>>>>>>>        //Report invalid driver
83062>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Invalid Driver - file" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber))
83062>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver (file number " * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * ")")
83062>>>>>>>        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver. File" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * "Driver" * Trim(MertechInc_DriverName) )
83063>>>>>>>>
83063>>>>>>>
83063>>>>>>>        //Set MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_Invalid_Driver so that the commands can
83063>>>>>>>        //determine if the driver is valid. MertechInc_FileNumber is use instead of
83063>>>>>>>        //MertechInc_DriverName as integer conparisons are quicker than string conparisons
83063>>>>>>>        Move MertechInc_Invalid_Driver to MertechInc_FileNumber
83064>>>>>>>    End
83064>>>>>>>>
83064>>>>>>>End_Procedure
83065>>>>>>>
83065>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83065>>>>>>>/// @Name        MertechInc_Pre_Size_String
83065>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string full of spaces.
83065>>>>>>>///
83065>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83065>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
83065>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     n/a
83065>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-12-02 By Gandalf Hernandez
83065>>>>>>>/// @See
83065>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_Pre_Size_String Global Integer iSize Returns String
83067>>>>>>>   Local String sWork
83067>>>>>>>   Local Integer iBlocks iRemainder
83067>>>>>>>
83067>>>>>>>   If (iSize <= 1) Begin
83069>>>>>>>      // marcelo 06/28/2000 implemented logic to avoid VDF 7 crashing problems
83069>>>>>>>          If FMAC_VERSION eq 7 Move 1000 to iSize
83072>>>>>>>          Else Move 16384 to iSize
83074>>>>>>>   End
83074>>>>>>>>
83074>>>>>>>
83074>>>>>>>   // Build the string in blocks of 32, to speed things up
83074>>>>>>>   // If the string is less than 32 bytes, just fill it up regularly
83074>>>>>>>   Move (iSize / 32) to iBlocks
83075>>>>>>>   Move (Mod(iSize, 32)) to iRemainder
83076>>>>>>>
83076>>>>>>>   If (iBlocks > 0) Begin
83078>>>>>>>      Move (Repeat("                                ", iBlocks)) to sWork
83079>>>>>>>      Move (Append (sWork, (Repeat(" ", iRemainder)))) to sWork
83080>>>>>>>   End
83080>>>>>>>>
83080>>>>>>>   Else Move (Repeat(" ", iSize)) to sWork
83082>>>>>>>
83082>>>>>>>   Function_Return sWork
83083>>>>>>>End_Function
83084>>>>>>>
83084>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
