83095>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     n/a
83095>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-08-17 By Ian Smith
83095>>>>>>>///
83095>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_Reset_DecSep Global
83097>>>>>>>    If MertechInc_iDecSep Ne 46 Set_Attribute DF_DECIMAL_SEPARATOR to MertechInc_iDecSep
83102>>>>>>>End_Procedure
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        FETCH_FIELD
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description Selects or de-selects the fields to be fetched during the
83103>>>>>>>/// next FIND (query).
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-07-16 By Ian Smith
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax FETCH_FIELD <FileNum> <FieldStart> THRU <FieldEnd> TO DF_FETCH_TRUE
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNum    is the File Number
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldStart is the Field Name or Number that will start the selection range
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldEnd   is the Field Name or Number that will finish the selection range
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax FETCH_FIELD <FileNum> <Field1> TO DF_FETCH_TRUE
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNum  is the File Number
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  Field1 Fields Name or Number to be selected
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this command to manually insert a string into a trace
83103>>>>>>>/// file. This can be useful for readability within the trace file to log
83103>>>>>>>/// what is actually happening at certain points.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions The text string is less than 80 characters long.
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 20013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
83103>>>>>>>/// @See         ENABLE_TRACE_ON DISABLE_TRACE_ON
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE {variable}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  {variable}          The string to insert into the trace file.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>/// Login "localhost" "mds" "mertech" "ora_drv"
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// ENABLE_TRACE_ON to "c:\trace.txt" DEBUG_LEVEL
83103>>>>>>>/// open Customer
83103>>>>>>>/// SQL_TEXT_MESSAGE "The table has been opened"
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name       SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to fetch only a certain number of fields
83103>>>>>>>/// while doing a "find". When specifying the field number to start from and
83103>>>>>>>/// field number to end on, the find will only fetch the given fields from the
83103>>>>>>>/// record. It is important to always use this command after first deselecting
83103>>>>>>>/// all columns i.e. setting RESET_FETCH_FIELDS to DF_FETCH_FALSE. Also, after
83103>>>>>>>/// using this command, all columns need to be reselected i.e. setting
83103>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS to DF_FETCH_TRUE. Note that fields used as a part the
83103>>>>>>>/// index segment associated with the find will always be fetched regardless.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 20014-04-30 by Marcello Yo
83103>>>>>>>/// @See         RESET_FETCH_FIELDS DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND {FileNumber} {fieldStart} THRU {fieldEnd}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  fieldStart          The field number to start the fetch from
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FieldEnd            The field number to end the fetch at
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83103>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS  CUSTOMER DF_FETCH_FALSE
83103>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND CUSTOMER CUSTOMER_NUMBER NAME
83103>>>>>>>/// DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS DISABLED
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// Clear Customer
83103>>>>>>>/// Repeat
83103>>>>>>>///    Find Gt Customer by Index.1
83103>>>>>>>///    If (Found) Showln Customer.Customer_Number '-' Customer.Name
83103>>>>>>>/// Until (Not(Found))
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS Customer DF_FETCH_TRUE
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        RESET_FETCH_FIELDS
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to specify whether to retrieve all columns
83103>>>>>>>/// or no columns when performing a find. It is usually used with the command
83103>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND to reset the column fetching. This command can either be
83103>>>>>>>/// set to DF_FETCH_TRUE, which will fetch all columns or set to DF_FETCH_FALSE,
83103>>>>>>>/// which will fetch no columns.
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2014-04-30 by Marcello Yo
83103>>>>>>>/// @See         SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax RESET_FETCH_FIELDS {FileNumber} {DF_FETCH_TRUE/DF_FETCH_FALSE}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber                  The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  DF_FETCH_TRUE               fetch all columns
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  DF_FETCH_FALSE              fetch no columns
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83103>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS  CUSTOMER DF_FETCH_FALSE
83103>>>>>>>/// SELECT_COLUMNS_FIND CUSTOMER CUSTOMER_NUMBER NAME
83103>>>>>>>/// DISABLE_SELECT_COLUMNS_ERRORS DISABLED
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// Clear Customer
83103>>>>>>>/// Repeat
83103>>>>>>>///    Find Gt Customer by Index.1
83103>>>>>>>///    If (Found) Showln Customer.Customer_Number '-' Customer.Name
83103>>>>>>>/// Until (Not(Found))
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// RESET_FETCH_FIELDS Customer DF_FETCH_TRUE
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_FOR_ONEROW
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description This command will instruct the driver to fetch one row
83103>>>>>>>/// per query
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
83103>>>>>>>/// @See
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_FOR_ONEROW {FileNumber}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>///     open Customer
83103>>>>>>>///     SQL_FOR_ONEROW Customer.File_Number
83103>>>>>>>///     Repeat
83103>>>>>>>///             find gt Customer by Recnum
83103>>>>>>>///         If (Found) Begin
83103>>>>>>>///             showln "Sales name is " Customer.FirstName
83103>>>>>>>///         end
83103>>>>>>>///     until (Customer.ID = 10)
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_REFRESH_CACHE
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description For optimization during record retrieval, a set number of
83103>>>>>>>/// records are stored in a local cache. This command forces a refresh, by
83103>>>>>>>/// making the next find retrieve the record from the database instead of
83103>>>>>>>/// the cache.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-19 by Aaron Gulack
83103>>>>>>>/// @See
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_REFRESH_CACHE OF {FileNumber}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// Find gt Customer by Index.1
83103>>>>>>>/// While (Found) Begin
83103>>>>>>>///     showln "Customer name is " CUSTOMER.CUSTOMER
83103>>>>>>>/// Loop
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// SQL_REFRESH_CACHE of CUSTOMER
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_FOR_SET
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description Use this command during LT or GT finds to only fetch a set
83103>>>>>>>/// number of rows. An option is also available for this command to disable
83103>>>>>>>/// the local cash by passing NOCACHE at the end of the command call. Note
83103>>>>>>>/// that if the rowcount is set low, too many round-trips to the server may
83103>>>>>>>/// result, effecting performance significantly. Also, if the rowcount is set
83103>>>>>>>/// too high a large number of records can be pre-fetched and end up not being
83103>>>>>>>/// used by the application. Because of this, the default of 10 rows and a cache
83103>>>>>>>/// will be adequate for most situations.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
83103>>>>>>>/// @See
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_FOR_SET {FileNumber} MAXROWS {variable} {CACHE/NOCACHE}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable            The maximum number of rows to retrieve
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  CACHE               fetched rows will be kept at the local cache
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  NOCACHE             fetched rows will not be kept at the local cache
83103>>>>>>>/// @Example
83103>>>>>>>/// Open Customer
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// SQL_FOR_SET Customer MAXROWS 15 CACHE
83103>>>>>>>/// find gt Customer by Index.1
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83103>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_SET
83103>>>>>>>/// @Description Initializes and sets an initial statement for embedded
83103>>>>>>>/// sql execution.
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions Parameter may be more than 255 characters long so redirect to method.
83103>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
83103>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83103>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
83103>>>>>>>/// @See         SQL_SET_STMT
83103>>>>>>>///
83103>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SQL_SET {FileNumber}
83103>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber          The number of the file
83103>>>>>>>
83103>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_SQL_SET Global String sStatement
83105>>>>>>>    Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function 1 CALLBACK 0 PASSING MertechInc_Blank sStatement 0 RESULT MertechInc_iRet
83110>>>>>>>End_Procedure
83111>>>>>>>
83111>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83111>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_APPEND
83111>>>>>>>/// @Description Appends a string value to the current embedded sql statement
83111>>>>>>>/// already set.
83111>>>>>>>///
83111>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions Parameter may be more than 255 characters long so redirect to method.
83111>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
83111>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83111>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-08-20 by Aaron Gulack
83111>>>>>>>/// @See                 SQL_APPEND_STMT
83111>>>>>>>
83111>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_SQL_APPEND Global String sStatement
83113>>>>>>>    Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function 2 CALLBACK 0 PASSING MertechInc_Blank sStatement 0 RESULT MertechInc_iRet
83118>>>>>>>End_Procedure
83119>>>>>>>
83119>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83119>>>>>>>/// @Name        SQL_EXECUTE
83119>>>>>>>/// @Description Executes the current embedded SQL statement set and commits
