84058>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84058>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set the number of milliseconds
84058>>>>>>>/// an SQL statement waits for a database lock to be released before timing
84058>>>>>>>/// out. Locks are used with transactions to maintain atomicity. If a lock is
84058>>>>>>>/// not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and an error
84058>>>>>>>/// will be raised. By default, the timeout is set to -1, indicating that
84058>>>>>>>/// statements will wait indefinitely before timing out.
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84058>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84058>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84058>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
84058>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
84058>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
84058>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Number of milliseconds to wait until timeout
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Example
84058>>>>>>>/// SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to 6000
84058>>>>>>>
84058>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84058>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84058>>>>>>>/// @Description This command returns the number of milliseconds an SQL
84058>>>>>>>/// statement will wait for a database lock to be released. If the lock
84058>>>>>>>/// is not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and
84058>>>>>>>/// an error will be raised. Note that the default value is -1, indicating
84058>>>>>>>/// that the statement will wait indefinitely.
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84058>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84058>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84058>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
84058>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
84058>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
84058>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the number of milliseconds
84058>>>>>>>///
84058>>>>>>>/// @Example
84058>>>>>>>/// GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to iTimeout
84058>>>>>>>
