84076>>>>>>>/// @Name        CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to call a stored procedure on the SQL
84076>>>>>>>/// backend. To successfully call a procedure with this command, a string
84076>>>>>>>/// must be passed containing a valid procedure name. In addition, if the
84076>>>>>>>/// procedure takes any arguments, they must also be passed using the constant
84076>>>>>>>/// "passing" along with all of the needed arguments. If the procedure has a
84076>>>>>>>/// return value, then SQL_GET_FUNCTION_RETURN or SQL_FETCH_NEXT_ROW can be
84076>>>>>>>/// used to get the value(s). If an error is found then the indicator "Err"
84076>>>>>>>/// is set to true.
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84076>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84076>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84076>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-09-25 by Aaron Gulack
84076>>>>>>>/// @See
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Syntax CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE {procedure} Passing {variable}
84076>>>>>>>/// @Param procedure            Full name of the procedure
84076>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Argument being passed (can be multiple)
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Example
84076>>>>>>>/// CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_addmessage" passing 50003 15 "Please enter a valid date"
84076>>>>>>>
84076>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84076>>>>>>>/// @Name        CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to call a stored procedure on the SQL
84076>>>>>>>/// backend. To successfully call a procedure with this command, a string
84076>>>>>>>/// must be passed containing a valid procedure name. In addition, if the
84076>>>>>>>/// procedure takes any arguments, they must also be passed using the constant
84076>>>>>>>/// "passing" along with all of the needed arguments. If the procedure has a
84076>>>>>>>/// return value, then SQL_GET_FUNCTION_RETURN, SQL_FETCH_NEXT_ROW or
84076>>>>>>>/// GET_PROCEDURE_RETURN can be used to get the value(s). If an error is found
84076>>>>>>>/// then the indicator "Err" is set to true.
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
84076>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84076>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84076>>>>>>>/// @See                 CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Syntax CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE {procedure} Passing {variable}
84076>>>>>>>/// @Param procedure            Full name of the procedure
84076>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Argument to be passed (can be multiple)
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Example
84076>>>>>>>/// CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_addmessage" passing 50003 15 "Please enter a valid date"
84076>>>>>>>
84076>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84076>>>>>>>/// @Name        END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to close any open cursors created
84076>>>>>>>/// by the respective stored procedure. Cursors are used in MSSQL to make
84076>>>>>>>/// the results from one procedure temporarily available to other procedures
84076>>>>>>>/// or triggers. To avoid causing unwanted results, it is good practice to
84076>>>>>>>/// use this command once a procedure call is completed.
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84076>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84076>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84076>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84076>>>>>>>/// @See                 CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Syntax END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>///
84076>>>>>>>/// @Example
84076>>>>>>>/// CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_spaceused" Passing "Customer"
84076>>>>>>>/// GET_PROCEDURE_RETURN to sValue
84076>>>>>>>/// END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84076>>>>>>>/// Showln sValue
84076>>>>>>>
84076>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
