84106>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84106>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to find out how long until a
84106>>>>>>>/// specific temporary license for a driver expires. If 0 is returned,
84106>>>>>>>/// then the license is not a temporary license. If -1 is returned, then
84106>>>>>>>/// the license has already expired. Otherwise, the number returned
84106>>>>>>>/// is the number of days until the license will expire.
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84106>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84106>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84106>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 Aaron Gulack
84106>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to {variable}
84106>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the days until expiration
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Example
84106>>>>>>>/// GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to iExpire
84106>>>>>>>/// Showln iExpire
84106>>>>>>>
84106>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84106>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
84106>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set a custom warning message to
84106>>>>>>>/// be displayed when a temporary license for a driver is close to expiring.
84106>>>>>>>/// Note that since the license evaluation is done during Login and before
84106>>>>>>>/// any open calls, this command should be called before either of those.
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84106>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84106>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84106>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84106>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to {variable}
84106>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     New warning message for expiring license
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Example
84106>>>>>>>/// SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to "Your license is about to expire."
84106>>>>>>>/// Login "localhost" "" "" "sql_drv"
84106>>>>>>>
84106>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84106>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH
84106>>>>>>>/// @Description This command will return the current path of the license
84106>>>>>>>/// associated with the driver.
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84106>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
84106>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84106>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-01 by Aaron Gulack
84106>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84106>>>>>>>///
84106>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH to {variable}
84106>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the path of the license
84106>>>>>>>
84106>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH Global Returns String
84108>>>>>>>    Local String sReturnValue
84108>>>>>>>
84108>>>>>>>    DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME 0
84110>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_FileNumber <> -1) Begin
84112>>>>>>>        Get MertechInc_Pre_Size_String 4096 to sReturnValue
84113>>>>>>>        Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function CALLDRV_LICENSE_ENVIRONMENT_SET CALLBACK 0 PASSING sReturnValue MertechInc_Blank CALLDRV_LICENSE_PATH RESULT MertechInc_iRet
84118>>>>>>>        If MertechInc_iRet EQ -1 INDICATE ERR True
84121>>>>>>>    End
84121>>>>>>>>
84121>>>>>>>
84121>>>>>>>    Function_Return sReturnValue
84122>>>>>>>End_Function
