85846>>>>>>>End_Enumeration_List
85846>>>>>>>
85846>>>>>>>// SQL Back-ends (iSQLDbType in the tSQLKeywords struct).
85846>>>>>>>// They can have slightly different SQL keywords. 
85846>>>>>>>// Note: If a new type is added to the list,
85846>>>>>>>//       the struct array xxx must be adjusted
85846>>>>>>>//       so that it is filled with all SQL
85846>>>>>>>//       keywords for that new type.
85846>>>>>>>Enum_List
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMSSQL
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMySQL
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeOracle
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDB2 
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypePostgre 
85846>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDataFlex // Embedded database.
85846>>>>>>>End_Enum_List 
85846>>>>>>>
85846>>>>>>>// We need to have our "own" constants for the standard DataFlex data types.
85846>>>>>>>// These can be used with SQL functions such as e.g. SQLColumnAdd, instead
85846>>>>>>>// of using one of the driver specific integer constants such as e.g. "SQL_VARCHAR".
85846>>>>>>>// We need to re-define the standard constants because several driver constants
85846>>>>>>>// have the same value and we need to be able to distinguish which data type to use when
85846>>>>>>>// e.g. creating a column with embedded SQL (ESQL).
85846>>>>>>>Enum_List 
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_ASCII_DUF     for 1500
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_BCD_DUF       for 1499
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_BINARY_DUF    for 1494
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATE_DUF      for 1498
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATETIME_DUF  for 1493
85846>>>>>>>    Define DF_TEXT_DUF      for 1495
85846>>>>>>>End_Enum_List
85846>>>>>>>
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMSSQL       for "Microsoft SQL Server"
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMySQL       for "MySQL"
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeOracle      for "Oracle"
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDB2         for "IBM DB2"
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypePostgre     for "PostgreSQL"
85846>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDataFlex    for "DataFlex Embedded"
85846>>>>>>>
85846>>>>>>>    Define SQL_TEXT for (DF_TEXT + 1024)
85846>>>>>>>
85846>>>>>>>Define SQL_CHARBIT          for (DF_BINARY + 1024)
85846>>>>>>>Define SQL_LONGVARCHARBIT   for (DF_BINARY + 1025)
85846>>>>>>>Define SQL_VARCHARBIT       for (DF_BINARY + 1026)
85846>>>>>>>
