86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//nLength:
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Specifies the size, in bytes, of this structure. Set this value to the size of the
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES structure.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Windows NT: Some functions that use the SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES structure do not verify the
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// value of the nLength member. However, an application should still set it properly.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// That ensures current, future, and cross-platform compatibility.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//lpSecurityDescriptor:
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Points to a security descriptor for the object that controls the sharing of it.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// If NULL is specified for this member, the object may be assigned the default security
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// descriptor of the calling process.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//bInheritHandle:
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Specifies whether the returned handle is inherited when a new process is created.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// If this member is TRUE, the new process inherits the handle.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// BOOL CreateDirectory(
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    LPCTSTR lpPathName,
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    LPSECURITY_ATTRIBUTES lpSecurityAttributes  // pointer to a security descriptor
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//   );
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// lpPathName
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  Points to a null-terminated string that specifies the path of the directory
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  to be created.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  There is a default string size limit for paths of MAX_PATH characters.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  This limit is related to how the CreateDirectory function parses paths.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// lpSecurityAttributes
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  Pointer to a SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES structure als called a security descriptor that
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  determines whether the returned handle can be inherited by child processes.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  If lpSecurityAttributes is NULL, the handle cannot be inherited.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Returns:
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  If the function succeeds, the return value is nonzero.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>//  If the function fails, the return value is zero. To get extended error information, call GetLastError.
86125>>>>>>>>>>>>>External_function vWin32_CreateDirectory "CreateDirectoryA" kernel32.dll ;  Pointer lpPathName Pointer lpSecurity_Attributes Returns Integer
