86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>// This function formats the time in a picture-string passed
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    h         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    hh        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    H         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    HH        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    m         Minutes with no leading zero for single-digit minutes
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    mm        Minutes with leading zero for single-digit minutes
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    s         Seconds with no leading zero for single-digit seconds
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    ss        Seconds with leading zero for single-digit seconds
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    t         One character time marker string, such as A or P
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    tt        Multicharacter time marker string, such as AM or PM
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>// For example, to get the time string  "11:29:40 PM"
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    use the following picture string: "hh" : "mm" : "ss tt"
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86138>>>>>>>>>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetTimeFormat "GetTimeFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpTimeStr ;  Integer cchTime Returns Integer
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Courtesy Of Vincent Oorsprong
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>// This function formats the date in a picture-string passed
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    d         Day of month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit days.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    dd        Day of month as digits with leading zero for single-digit days.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    ddd       Day of week as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVOAYMAME value associated with the specified locale.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    dddd      Day of week as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SDAYNAME
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              value associated with the specified locale.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    M         Month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit months.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MM        Month as digits with leading zero for single-digit months.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MMM       Month as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVMONTHNAME value associated with the specified locale.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MMMM      Month as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SMONTHNAME value
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              associated with the specified locale.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    y         Year as last two digits, but with no leading zero for years less than 10.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    yy        Year as last two digits, but with leading zero for years less than 10.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    yyyy      Year represented hy full four digits.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    gg        Period/era string. The function uses the CAL_SERASTRING value associated
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              with the specified locale. This element is ignored if the date to be formatted
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              does not have an associated era or period string.
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>// For example, to get the date string  "Wed, Aug 31 94"
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>// use the following picture string:    "ddd","MMM dd yy"
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86139>>>>>>>>>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetDateFormat "GetDateFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpDateStr ;  Integer cchDate Returns Integer
86140>>>>>>>>>>>>>
