86143>>>>>>>>>>>//
86143>>>>>>>>>>>// Gets the string from the right of the last sStopChar in sFrom
86143>>>>>>>>>>>// If sStopChar has no occurences in the string an empty string is
86143>>>>>>>>>>>// returned.
86143>>>>>>>>>>>Function StringFromRightOfChar Global String sFrom String sStopChar Returns String
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sRetVal
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sChar
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iLength
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iPos
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  Boolean bStopChar
86145>>>>>>>>>>>  Move "" To sRetval
86146>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Length(sFrom)) To iLength
86147>>>>>>>>>>>  If ((iLength>0) And (Pos(sStopChar,sFrom) <> 0)) Begin
86149>>>>>>>>>>>    Move iLength   To iPos
86150>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (False)   To bStopChar
86151>>>>>>>>>>>    While Not bStopChar
86155>>>>>>>>>>>      Move (Mid(sFrom,1,iPos)) To sChar
86156>>>>>>>>>>>      Decrement iPos
86157>>>>>>>>>>>      If ((sChar=sStopChar) Or (iPos<1)) Begin
86159>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (True) To bStopChar
86160>>>>>>>>>>>      End
86160>>>>>>>>>>>>
86160>>>>>>>>>>>      Else Begin
86161>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (sChar+sRetVal) To sRetVal
86162>>>>>>>>>>>      End
86162>>>>>>>>>>>>
86162>>>>>>>>>>>    Loop
86163>>>>>>>>>>>>
86163>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86163>>>>>>>>>>>>
86163>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return sRetVal
86164>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // StringFromRightOfChar
86165>>>>>>>>>>>
86165>>>>>>>>>>>
86165>>>>>>>>>>>// Pre:  sFileName contains the complete path of the file.
86165>>>>>>>>>>>// Post: returns the complete path of the file.
86165>>>>>>>>>>>// This function is inspired on function SEQ_ExtractPathFromFileName of Sture Andersen.
86165>>>>>>>>>>>Function ParseFolderName Global String sFileName Returns String
86167>>>>>>>>>>>  String sFile
86167>>>>>>>>>>>  String sFolderName
86167>>>>>>>>>>>  String sDirSep // this is "\" for windows, or "/" for unix
86167>>>>>>>>>>>  MOve "" To sFolderName
86168>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (sysconf(SYSCONF_DIR_SEPARATOR)) To sDirSep
86169>>>>>>>>>>>  If sDirSep In sFileName Begin
86171>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (StringFromRightOfChar(sFileName,sDirSep)) To sFile
86172>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (Replace(sFile,sFileName,"")) To sFolderName
86173>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86173>>>>>>>>>>>>
86173>>>>>>>>>>>  Else If ":" In sFileName Begin
86176>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (StringFromRightOfChar(sFileName,":")) To sFile
86177>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (Replace(sFile,sFileName,"")) To sFolderName
86178>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86178>>>>>>>>>>>>
86178>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return sFolderName
86179>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // ParseFolderName
86180>>>>>>>>>>>
86180>>>>>>>>>>>
86180>>>>>>>>>>>// Pre:  sFileName contains the complete path of the file.
86180>>>>>>>>>>>// post: The returned filename has it's path removed, but will have a extension
86180>>>>>>>>>>>Function ParseFileName Global String sFileName Returns String
86182>>>>>>>>>>>  String sFolderName
86182>>>>>>>>>>>  String sDirSep // this is "\" for windows, or "/" for unix
86182>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (sysconf(SYSCONF_DIR_SEPARATOR)) To sDirSep
86183>>>>>>>>>>>  Get ParseFolderName sFileName To sFolderName
86184>>>>>>>>>>>  If (sFolderName <> "") Move (Replace(sFolderName,sFileName,"")) To sFileName
86187>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Replace(sDirSep,sFileName,"")) To sFileName
86188>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return sFilename
86189>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // ParseFileName
86190>>>>>>>>>>>
86190>>>>>>>>>>>
86190>>>>>>>>>>>// Pre:  sFileName may contain the complete path of the file.
86190>>>>>>>>>>>//       or contain multiple dots in the filename, so temp.gif.bak will
86190>>>>>>>>>>>//       return "bak" as the extension and not "gif"
86190>>>>>>>>>>>// Post: returns the extension only, this extension can be a valid unixlike extension
86190>>>>>>>>>>>//       such as "html" or "java"
86190>>>>>>>>>>>Function ParseFileExtension Global String sFileName Returns String
86192>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sFileExtension
86192>>>>>>>>>>>  Get StringFromRightOfChar sFileName "." To sFileExtension
86193>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return sFileExtension
86194>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // ParseFileExtension
86195>>>>>>>>>>>
86195>>>>>>>>>>>
86195>>>>>>>>>>>Define CS_DDE_ERR_UNKNOWN_LINE2   For ".\n"
86195>>>>>>>>>>>
86195>>>>>>>>>>>
86195>>>>>>>>>>>Function DDE_Error_To_String Integer iErrorID Returns String
86198>>>>>>>>>>>  String sMessage
86198>>>>>>>>>>>  Case Begin
86198>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND)
86200>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_FILE_NOT_FOUND To sMessage
86201>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86202>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vERROR_PATH_NOT_FOUND)
86205>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_PATH_NOT_FOUND To sMessage
86206>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86207>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vERROR_BAD_FORMAT)
86210>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_BAD_FORMAT To sMessage
86211>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86212>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_ACCESSDENIED)
86215>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_ACCESSDENIED To sMessage
86216>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86217>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_ASSOCINCOMPLETE)
86220>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_ASSOCINCOMPLETE To sMessage
86221>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86222>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_DDEBUSY)
86225>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_DDEBUSY To sMessage
86226>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86227>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_DDEFAIL)
86230>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_DDEFAIL To sMessage
86231>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86232>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_DDETIMEOUT)
86235>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_DDETIMEOUT To sMessage
86236>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86237>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_DLLNOTFOUND)
86240>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_DLLNOTFOUND To sMessage
86241>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86242>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_NOASSOC)
86245>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_NOASSOC To sMessage
86246>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86247>>>>>>>>>>>    Case ((iErrorID = vSE_ERR_OOM) Or (iErrorID = 0))
86250>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_OOM To sMessage
86251>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86252>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_PNF)
86255>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_PNF To sMessage
86256>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86257>>>>>>>>>>>    Case (iErrorID = vSE_ERR_SHARE)
86260>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_SHARE To sMessage
86261>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86262>>>>>>>>>>>    Case Else
86262>>>>>>>>>>>      Move CS_DDE_ERR_UNKNOWN_LINE1 To sMessage
86263>>>>>>>>>>>      Move (sMessage*Trim(iErrorID)*CS_DDE_ERR_UNKNOWN_LINE2) To sMessage
86264>>>>>>>>>>>      Case Break
86265>>>>>>>>>>>  Case End
86265>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return sMessage
86266>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // DDE_Error_To_String
86267>>>>>>>>>>>
86267>>>>>>>>>>>
86267>>>>>>>>>>>Procedure vDDE_Error_Handler Integer iErrorID
86270>>>>>>>>>>>  String sMessage
86270>>>>>>>>>>>  Get DDE_Error_To_String iErrorID To sMessage
86271>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sMessage CS_DDE_ERR_HANDL_PAKTC //  "Press a key to continue..."
86272>>>>>>>>>>>  Send Stop_Box sMessage CS_DDE_ERR_HANDL_CAPTION
86273>>>>>>>>>>>End_Procedure // vDDE_Error_Handler hInstance
86274>>>>>>>>>>>
86274>>>>>>>>>>>
86274>>>>>>>>>>>// Does the directory exist? - No = 0, Yes = 1
86274>>>>>>>>>>>// This also works with UNC path encoding and wildcards
86274>>>>>>>>>>>Function vFolderExists Global String sFolderName Returns Integer
86276>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sFolder sTmp
86276>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer bFolderExists iCh
86276>>>>>>>>>>>
86276>>>>>>>>>>>  // 2013-09-29 NGS Check for empty folder name and convert to ANSI
86276>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (ToANSI(Trim(sFolderName))) to sFolderName
86277>>>>>>>>>>>  If (sFolderName = "") Begin
86279>>>>>>>>>>>    Function_Return False
86280>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86280>>>>>>>>>>>>
86280>>>>>>>>>>>
86280>>>>>>>>>>>  Move dfTrue To bFolderExists
86281>>>>>>>>>>>  Move "dir:" To sFolder
86282>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sFolder sFolderName
86283>>>>>>>>>>>  Get Seq_New_Channel To iCh  // get free channel for input
86284>>>>>>>>>>>  Direct_Input Channel iCh sFolder
86286>>>>>>>>>>>    Repeat
86286>>>>>>>>>>>>
86286>>>>>>>>>>>      Readln Channel iCh sTmp
86288>>>>>>>>>>>      If (Trim(sTmp)="") Move dfFalse To bFolderExists
86291>>>>>>>>>>>      Else Begin
86292>>>>>>>>>>>        Move dfTrue To bFolderExists
86293>>>>>>>>>>>        Indicate seqeof True  // end loop
86294>>>>>>>>>>>        End
86294>>>>>>>>>>>>
86294>>>>>>>>>>>    Until (seqeof)
86296>>>>>>>>>>>  Close_Input Channel iCh
86298>>>>>>>>>>>  Send Seq_Release_Channel iCh
86299>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return bFolderExists
86300>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function  // vFolderExists
86301>>>>>>>>>>>
86301>>>>>>>>>>>
86301>>>>>>>>>>>// returns folder name if a folder was selected, otherwise returns ""
86301>>>>>>>>>>>Function vSHBrowseForFolder Global String sDialogTitle Returns String
86303>>>>>>>>>>>  String sFolder sBrowseInfo sTitle
86303>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpItemIdList lpsFolder lpsBrowseInfo lpsTitle
86303>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iFolderSelected iRetval
86303>>>>>>>>>>>
86303>>>>>>>>>>>  // fill string variable with null characters
86303>>>>>>>>>>>  ZeroType vtBrowseInfo To sBrowseInfo
86304>>>>>>>>>>>
86304>>>>>>>>>>>  If (sDialogTitle<>"") Begin
86306>>>>>>>>>>>    Move sDialogTitle To sTitle
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    // Torben Lund suggested converting the string with toansi. Doing it like that
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    // disables showing some commonly used ascii characters like ascii 137 (‰)
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    // These chars are correctly shown if no toansi is used.
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    // I can imagine that he wanted to path to be ANSI, but as long as it isa just
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    // selected it will always be valid.
86307>>>>>>>>>>>    GetAddress Of sTitle To lpsTitle
86308>>>>>>>>>>>    Put lpsTitle To sBrowseInfo At vtBrowseInfo.lpszTitle
86309>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86309>>>>>>>>>>>>
86309>>>>>>>>>>>
86309>>>>>>>>>>>  Put vBIF_RETURNONLYFSDIRS To sBrowseInfo At vtBrowseInfo.ulFlags
86310>>>>>>>>>>>
86310>>>>>>>>>>>  // Torben Lund added line below. Move handle of focus object to structure before
86310>>>>>>>>>>>  // calling function. Otherwise, the folderdialog will be started as a seperate task.
86310>>>>>>>>>>>  Put (window_handle(focus(desktop))) To sBrowseInfo At vtBrowseInfo.hWndOwner
86311>>>>>>>>>>>
86311>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sBrowseInfo To lpsBrowseInfo
86312>>>>>>>>>>>
86312>>>>>>>>>>>  // null 128 chars into var (make space)
86312>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Repeat(Character(0), vMAX_PATH)) To sFolder
86313>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sFolder To lpsFolder
86314>>>>>>>>>>>
86314>>>>>>>>>>>  // select folder
86314>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (vWin32_SHBrowseForFolder(lpsBrowseInfo)) To lpItemIdList
86315>>>>>>>>>>>  // get selected folder name
86315>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (vWin32_SHGetPathFromIDList(lpItemIdList, lpsFolder)) To iFolderSelected
86316>>>>>>>>>>>
86316>>>>>>>>>>>  // release memory resources that are used by the ItemIdList
86316>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (vWin32_CoTaskMemFree(lpItemIdList)) To iRetval
86317>>>>>>>>>>>
86317>>>>>>>>>>>  If (iFolderSelected<>0) Function_Return (CString(sFolder))
86320>>>>>>>>>>>  Else Function_Return ""
86322>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // vSHBrowseForFolder
86323>>>>>>>>>>>
86323>>>>>>>>>>>
86323>>>>>>>>>>>// returns 0 if the folder is created.
86323>>>>>>>>>>>//         1 if the API-call returned an error.
86323>>>>>>>>>>>Function vCreateDirectory Global String sNewFolder Returns Integer
86325>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sFolder sSA
86325>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsFolder lpsSecurity_Attributes lpDescriptor
86325>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iRetval bFolderCreated bInheritHandle
86325>>>>>>>>>>>
86325>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (False) To bFolderCreated
86326>>>>>>>>>>>  // fill string variable with null characters
86326>>>>>>>>>>>  ZeroType vtSecurity_attributes To sSA
86327>>>>>>>>>>>
86327>>>>>>>>>>>  // null MAX_PATH chars into var (make space)
86327>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Repeat(Character(0), vMAX_PATH)) To sFolder
86328>>>>>>>>>>>
86328>>>>>>>>>>>  If (sNewFolder <> "") Begin
86330>>>>>>>>>>>
86330>>>>>>>>>>>    Move dfTrue To  bInheritHandle
86331>>>>>>>>>>>    // Setting this to NULL is already done by the zerotype command
86331>>>>>>>>>>>    // Move NULL   To  lpDescriptor
86331>>>>>>>>>>>    Put (length(sSA))   To sSA At vtSecurity_attributes.nLength
86332>>>>>>>>>>>    //Put lpDescriptor To sSA at vtSecurity_attributes.lpDescriptor
86332>>>>>>>>>>>    Put bInheritHandle To sSA At vtSecurity_attributes.bInheritHandle
86333>>>>>>>>>>>
86333>>>>>>>>>>>    GetAddress Of sSA To lpsSecurity_Attributes
86334>>>>>>>>>>>
86334>>>>>>>>>>>    //
86334>>>>>>>>>>>    Move sNewFolder To sFolder
86335>>>>>>>>>>>    GetAddress Of sFolder To lpsFolder
86336>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (vWin32_CreateDirectory(lpsFolder, lpsSecurity_Attributes)) To bFolderCreated
86337>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86337>>>>>>>>>>>>
86337>>>>>>>>>>>
86337>>>>>>>>>>>  Ifnot bFolderCreated Move 1 To iRetVal
86340>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return iRetVal
86341>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // vCreateDirectory
86342>>>>>>>>>>>
86342>>>>>>>>>>>
86342>>>>>>>>>>>// **WvA: 03-02-2002 Function created.
86342>>>>>>>>>>>// With this function one can remove a directory.
86342>>>>>>>>>>>// returns 0 if the folder is removed.
86342>>>>>>>>>>>//         1 if the API-call returned an error (Use GetLastError API to get the details)
86342>>>>>>>>>>>//         2 if the folder did not exist
86342>>>>>>>>>>>//         3 if the sFolder parameter passed is equal to ""
86342>>>>>>>>>>>Function vRemoveDirectory Global String sFolder Returns Integer
86344>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sPath
86344>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsPath
86344>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iRetval bRemoved bExists
86344>>>>>>>>>>>
86344>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (False) To bRemoved
86345>>>>>>>>>>>  Move 0 To iRetVal
86346>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Trim(sFolder)) To sFolder
86347>>>>>>>>>>>  If (sFolder="") Begin
86349>>>>>>>>>>>    Move 3 To iRetVal
86350>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86350>>>>>>>>>>>>
86350>>>>>>>>>>>  If (vFolderExists(sFolder)=False) Begin
86352>>>>>>>>>>>    Move 2 To iRetVal
86353>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86353>>>>>>>>>>>>
86353>>>>>>>>>>>  If (iRetVal=0) Begin
86355>>>>>>>>>>>    // null MAX_PATH chars into var (make space)
86355>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (Repeat(Character(0), vMAX_PATH)) To sPath
86356>>>>>>>>>>>    //
86356>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (Insert(sFolder,sPath,1)) To sPath
86357>>>>>>>>>>>    GetAddress Of sPath To lpsPath
86358>>>>>>>>>>>    Move (vWin32_RemoveDirectory(lpsPath)) To bRemoved
86359>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86359>>>>>>>>>>>>
86359>>>>>>>>>>>
86359>>>>>>>>>>>  If ((iRetVal=0) And (bRemoved=False)) Begin
86361>>>>>>>>>>>    Move 1 To iRetVal
86362>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86362>>>>>>>>>>>>
86362>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return iRetVal
86363>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // vRemoveDirectory
86364>>>>>>>>>>>
86364>>>>>>>>>>>
86364>>>>>>>>>>>
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// This function informs the user that he entered a yet unknown folder and
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// asks if he/she wants to create the folder (Yes/No)
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// Choice: "Yes" - this creates the folder
86364>>>>>>>>>>>//                 if successful, the function returns false
86364>>>>>>>>>>>//                 else it will be true.
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// Choice: "No"  - returns TRUE, This allows the programmer to take action
86364>>>>>>>>>>>//                 For example: to stop a save
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// Precondition: A foldername must be entered. We do not check for empty paths
86364>>>>>>>>>>>// This function returns a non-zero value if the folder isn't created afterwards
86364>>>>>>>>>>>Function vVerifyNewFolder Global String sFolderName Returns Integer
86366>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer bIsNotValid
86366>>>>>>>>>>>  Integer iUsers_Choice
86366>>>>>>>>>>>  String  sMessage
86366>>>>>>>>>>>
86366>>>>>>>>>>>  If (vFolderExists(sFolderName) Eq 0) Begin
86368>>>>>>>>>>>    Move "The folder '" To sMessage
86369>>>>>>>>>>>    Append sMessage sFolderName
86370>>>>>>>>>>>    Append sMessage "' does not yet exist,\n"
86371>>>>>>>>>>>    Append sMessage "Do you want to create it now?"
86372>>>>>>>>>>>    Get YesNo_Box sMessage "Confirm" MB_DefButton1 To iUsers_Choice
86373>>>>>>>>>>>    Case Begin
86373>>>>>>>>>>>      Case (iUsers_Choice = MBR_Yes)
86375>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (vCreateDirectory(sFolderName)) To bIsNotValid
86376>>>>>>>>>>>        If bIsNotValid Begin
86378>>>>>>>>>>>          Move "An error occurred while trying to create folder '" To sMessage
86379>>>>>>>>>>>          Append sMessage sFolderName "'.\n\n"
86381>>>>>>>>>>>          Send Info_Box sMessage "Info"
86382>>>>>>>>>>>          End
86382>>>>>>>>>>>>
86382>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Break
86383>>>>>>>>>>>      Case (iUsers_Choice = MBR_No)
86386>>>>>>>>>>>        Move dfTrue To bIsNotValid // Cancel the save
86387>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Break
86388>>>>>>>>>>>    Case End
86388>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86388>>>>>>>>>>>>
86388>>>>>>>>>>>  Function_Return bIsNotValid
86389>>>>>>>>>>>End_Function // vVerifyNewFolder
86390>>>>>>>>>>>
86390>>>>>>>>>>>
86390>>>>>>>>>>>// This will perform an operation on a file (e.g. open) with the application
86390>>>>>>>>>>>// registered in the Windows Registry to open that type of file (via its extension)
86390>>>>>>>>>>>// sOperation would be "OPEN" (it could also be "PRINT" etc).
86390>>>>>>>>>>>Procedure vShellExecute global String sOperation String sDocument String sParameters String sPath
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Handle  hInstance hWnd
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsOperation
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsDocument
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsParameters
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Pointer lpsPath
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  // remove any leading/trailing spaces in the string
86392>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Trim(sDocument)) To sDocument
86393>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (Trim(sPath))     To sPath
86394>>>>>>>>>>>  // Make the strings readable for windows API, by converting them to null-terminated
86394>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sOperation   (Character(0))
86395>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sDocument    (Character(0))
86396>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sParameters  (Character(0))
86397>>>>>>>>>>>  Append sPath        (Character(0))
86398>>>>>>>>>>>  // Connect the corresponding pointers to the strings
86398>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sOperation  To lpsOperation
86399>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sDocument   To lpsDocument
86400>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sParameters To lpsParameters
86401>>>>>>>>>>>  GetAddress Of sPath       To lpsPath
86402>>>>>>>>>>>
86402>>>>>>>>>>>  Get Window_Handle To hWnd
86403>>>>>>>>>>>  Move (vWin32_ShellExecute (hWnd, lpsOperation, lpsDocument, lpsParameters, lpsPath, 1)) To hInstance
86404>>>>>>>>>>>  If (hInstance <= 32) Begin
86406>>>>>>>>>>>    Send vDDE_Error_Handler hInstance
86407>>>>>>>>>>>  End
86407>>>>>>>>>>>>
86407>>>>>>>>>>>End_Procedure // vShellExecute
86408>>>>>>>>>>>
86408>>>>>>>>>>>
86408>>>>>>>>>>>Class cShellFileOperations Is a Array
