87630>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87630>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure SQLBindFile Integer iFileNum
87632>>>>>>>>>>>>>        tColumnMap tColumnMap
87632>>>>>>>>>>>>>        tColumnMap tColumnMap
87632>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String[] sBindFileColumns
87633>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer[] iBufferColumn
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iColCnt i iDateFormat iResultColumnType iBindFileColumnType
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String sColumnName
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Variant vFieldValue
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Boolean isRecnumTable
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87634>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87648>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87648>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87648>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of iFileNum to isRecnumTable
87651>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get ptColumnMap to tColumnMap
87652>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87652>>>>>>>>>>>>>        If (tColumnMap.iFileNum <> iFileNum) Begin
87654>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Move iFileNum to tColumnMap.iFileNum
87655>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87655>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // First we build an array of the column names (in order) from the file buffer to bind to
87655>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_FILE_NUMBER_FIELDS of iFileNum to iColCnt
87658>>>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 0 to iColCnt
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (isRecnumTable) Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NAME of iFileNum i to sColumnName
87669>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Else Move "" to sColumnName
87671>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87671>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move (Uppercase(sColumnName)) to sBindFileColumns[i]
87672>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // Next we iterate over the columns in the resultset.  Any column names that match we 
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // set its match location into an array that maps each resultset column to its matching
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column number in the file buffer.  If there is no match, we set that resultset
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column mappped column to -1.
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            //
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // Since Arrays are zero based and columns are numbered from 1, when we actually map
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // to set the value, we need to add 1 to array indexer to get the proper resultset
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column AND we need to add 1 to the mapped-to column since it was loaded into a zero
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // based array also.  (Ex: vResultColumn[0] = 2 means column 1 from the resultset maps
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // to Column 3 of the file buffer)
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87673>>>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_GET_NUM_COLS to iColCnt
87683>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87683>>>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 1 to iColCnt
87689>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87689>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_NAME i to sColumnName
87705>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87705>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // Because SearchArray returns -1 if there isn't a match, we don't need to do
87705>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // anything to make an "unmapped column" have a value of -1.
87705>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move (SearchArray(Uppercase(sColumnName), sBindFileColumns)) to tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // If the types don't match between the columns, then "unmap" the column.  This
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // should only occur when you're not mapping to the same file as the resultset.
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // In this case, sql.pkg silently does nothing, so we need to duplicate this instead
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // of generating an error.  If the mapping is to a string, then any type can be
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // converted to a string so its okay.
87706>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1] <> -1) Begin
87708>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of i DFTYPE to iResultColumnType
87725>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87725>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_TYPE of iFileNum (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]) to iBindFileColumnType
87728>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    
87728>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // If the conversion is to string (even if the resultset column is something
87728>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // else) its ok, so Break out of the If block before we muck things up.
87728>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iBindFileColumnType = DF_ASCII) Break
87731>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87731>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // Otherwise, break the mapping
87731>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iResultColumnType <> iBindFileColumnType) Move -1 to tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]
87734>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End
87734>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87734>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
87735>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87735>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87735>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Set ptColumnMap to tColumnMap
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>        End
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to iDateFormat
87737>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to True
87738>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Clear iFileNum
87739>>>>>>>>>>>>>        For i from 0 to (SizeOfArray(tColumnMap.vResultColumn)-1)
87745>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87745>>>>>>>>>>>>>            If (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i] > -1) Begin
87747>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_FETCH_COLUMN (i+1) into vFieldValue
87752>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Set_Field_Value iFileNum (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i]) to vFieldValue
87755>>>>>>>>>>>>>            End
87755>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87755>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Loop
87756>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87756>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set_Attribute DF_FILE_STATUS of iFileNum to DF_FILE_ACTIVE
87759>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to iDateFormat
87760>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
87761>>>>>>>>>>>>>    
87761>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLGetData Integer iCol Integer iLen Returns String
87763>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String data
87763>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer retlen
87763>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87763>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87777>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87777>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87777>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CHUNK_SIZE to iLen
87794>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87794>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_DATA_CHUNK COLUMN iCol OFFSET (piDataChunkOffset(Self)) to data retlen
87804>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87804>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set piDataChunkOffset to (piDataChunkOffset(Self)+retlen)
87805>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87805>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return data
87806>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87807>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87807>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLColumnMap String sColname Returns Integer
87809>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iNumColumns i iIndex
87809>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String[] cols
87810>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87810>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87824>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87824>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87824>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get SQLStmtAttribute SQLSTMTATTRIB_COLUMNCOUNT to iNumColumns
87825>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87825>>>>>>>>>>>>>        For i from 1 to iNumColumns
87831>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87831>>>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_GET_COL_NAME i to cols[i-1]
87847>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87847>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Move (trim(Uppercase(cols[i-1]))) to cols[i-1]
87848>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Loop
87849>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87849>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87849>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (trim(Uppercase(sColname))) to sColname
87850>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (SearchArray(sColname, cols)) to iIndex
87851>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return (iIndex+1)  // even if searcharray returns -1 (not found) this expects 0 for not found, so it's ok
87852>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87853>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87853>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLStmtAttribute Integer iAttribId Returns String
87855>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iCnt
87855>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87855>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87869>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87869>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87869>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Begin
87869>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_COLUMNCOUNT)
87871>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_NUM_COLS to iCnt
87881>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87881>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return iCnt
87882>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87883>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_ROWCOUNT)
87886>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_NUM_ROWS to iCnt
87896>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87896>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87896>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver doesn't know the rowcount before the first fetch.
87896>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
87898>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (pisBeforeFetch(Self)) Function_Return -1
87901>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End
87901>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87901>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87901>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return iCnt
87902>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87903>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_ROWCOUNT_TYPE)
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // TODO: Need something to indicate the quality of the SQL_GET_NUM_ROWS, or fake till I make it
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87907>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_NUMMESSAGES)
87910>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return -1
87911>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // TODO: Are the messages returned in SQLGetMessage from the driver, or from the underlying connection?
87911>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87912>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case Else
87912>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case End
87912>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87912>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87913>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87913>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLColAttribute Integer iCol Integer iAttribId Returns String
87915>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String sValue
87915>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iSQLType
87915>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iDFType
87915>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87915>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87929>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87929>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol SQLTYPE to iSQLType
87946>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87946>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DFTYPE to iDFType
87963>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87963>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87963>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Begin
87963>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_SIZE)
87965>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol SIZE to sValue
87982>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87982>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87982>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
87982>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
87984>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=12) Move (Integer(sValue-1)) to sValue
87987>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iDFType=5) Move "0" to sValue
87990>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=40)  Move "10" to sValue
87993>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
87993>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87993>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87993>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87994>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_PRECISION)
87997>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DECIMALS to sValue
88014>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88014>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88015>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_LABEL)
88018>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol COLUMN_NAME to sValue
88035>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88035>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88036>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_BASECOLUMNNAME)
88039>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol COLUMN_NAME to sValue
88056>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88056>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88056>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver doesn't use Base Column Name. 
88056>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88058>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    Move "" to sValue   
88059>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88059>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88059>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
88059>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88060>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_BASETABLENAME)
88063>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol TABLE_NAME to sValue
88080>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88080>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88081>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_SQLTYPE)
88084>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move iSQLType to sValue
88085>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88085>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
88085>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88087>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=2) Move "3" to sValue
88090>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=-99) Move "12" to sValue
88093>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=40)  Move "91" to sValue
88096>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88096>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88096>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
88096>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88097>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_NULLABLE)
88100>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol NULLABLE to sValue
88117>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88117>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88118>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_DFTYPE)
88121>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DFTYPE to sValue
88138>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88138>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88138>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
88138>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88140>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iDFType = 5) Move "0" to sValue
88143>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88143>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88143>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88144>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case End
88144>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
88144>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sValue
88145>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
88146>>>>>>>>>>>>>
