89869>>>>>>>// The cConnection class is the new SQL connections class for DF 19.
89869>>>>>>>// If an object of the cConnection class hasn't been instantiated we use a "dummy" class in its place.
89869>>>>>>>
89869>>>>>>>// We're making references to this object handle so we need it defined
89869>>>>>>>// here as well as for the cDbUpdateHandler class
89869>>>>>>>
89869>>>>>>>    Global_Variable Handle ghoSQLConnectionHandler
89869>>>>>>>    
89869>>>>>>>Class cSQLConnectionHandler is a cObject  
89870>>>>>>>    
89870>>>>>>>    Procedure Construct_Object
89872>>>>>>>        Forward Send Construct_Object
89874>>>>>>>        Move Self to ghoSQLConnectionHandler
89875>>>>>>>        
89875>>>>>>>        Property Handle phoSQLConnectionIniFile (Create(Self,RefClass(cSQLConnectionIniFile))) 
89876>>>>>>>        
89876>>>>>>>        // These properties are used by the cDbUpdateVersion and cDbUpdateFunctionLibrary classes,
89876>>>>>>>        // but put here so they can be set/get in both class objects. Those classes has "relay"
89876>>>>>>>        // methods to this class.
89876>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbUseConnectionID True
89877>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbToANSI          True
89878>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbRecnum          True
89879>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbCopyData        True
89880>>>>>>>
89880>>>>>>>        // Driver default value settings:
89880>>>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
89880>>>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
89880>>>>>>>        // Sample: Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_NUMERIC of {driverNumber} to {StringVariable}
89880>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueASCII    ""
89881>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueBinary   ""
89882>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDate     ""
89883>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDateTime ""
89884>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueNumeric  ""
89885>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueText     ""
89886>>>>>>>        
89886>>>>>>>        // Driver "nullability" settings:
89886>>>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
89886>>>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
89886>>>>>>>        // Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_ASCII of {driverNumber} to {BooleanVariable}
89886>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableASCII    False
89887>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableBinary   False
89888>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDate     False
89889>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDateTime False
89890>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableNumeric  False
89891>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableText     False
89892>>>>>>>
89892>>>>>>>        // *** This is the central point of connection data for the Database Update Framework ***
89892>>>>>>>        //     It is private because the get/set version also updates the DAW/Mertech
89892>>>>>>>        //     driver interfaces.
89892>>>>>>>        //     There are also procedure/function pairs to set/get individual data members
89892>>>>>>>        //     of the struct they are all routed throu this struct property.
89892>>>>>>>        Property tSQLConnection Private.pSQLConnection
89893>>>>>>>
89893>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
89894>>>>>>>    
89894>>>>>>>    Procedure End_Construct_Object             
89896>>>>>>>        Boolean bReadSettings 
89896>>>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
89896>>>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
89896>>>>>>>
89896>>>>>>>        Forward Send End_Construct_Object
89898>>>>>>>
89898>>>>>>>        // Now is the time to read and apply SQL connection settings.
89898>>>>>>>        Get SetupSQLConnection True to SQLConnection   
89899>>>>>>>        // ToDo: Should we use two pSQLConnection properties; one for the "from" database (in case of not Embedded);
89899>>>>>>>        //       and one for the "to" database??
89899>>>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection
89900>>>>>>>    End_Procedure    
89901>>>>>>>    
89901>>>>>>>    // *** Properties ***
89901>>>>>>>    // All connection related "properties" (get/set pairs) are really done by changing the
89901>>>>>>>    // private.pSQLConnection struct connection property. These "properties" are 
89901>>>>>>>    // merely here for conveniance.
89901>>>>>>>    //           
89901>>>>>>>    // The pSQLConnection get/set are here so we have a "central hub"
89901>>>>>>>    // where we update data to/from the DAW & Mertech driver interfaces and this framework.
89901>>>>>>>    // This struct property contains all the connection data.
89901>>>>>>>    //
89901>>>>>>>    Procedure Set pSQLConnection tSQLConnection SQLConnection
89903>>>>>>>        Boolean bIsDaw bIsMertech bOK
89903>>>>>>>        
89903>>>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection 
89904>>>>>>>        
89904>>>>>>>        // When starting a program we might not have a connection id yet:
89904>>>>>>>        If (SQLConnection.sConnectionID = "" or SQLConnection.sDriverID = DATAFLEX_ID) Begin
89906>>>>>>>            Procedure_Return
89907>>>>>>>        End                 
89907>>>>>>>>
89907>>>>>>>        
89907>>>>>>>        // After we have set the class property we need to tell the DAW/Mertech
89907>>>>>>>        // driver interfaces about the change & make a new login.
89907>>>>>>>        Get SQLLogin SQLConnection to bOK
89908>>>>>>>        If (bOK = False) Begin
89910>>>>>>>            Error DFERR_PROGRAM "Login error."       
89911>>>>>>>>
89911>>>>>>>        End 
89911>>>>>>>>
89911>>>>>>>        
89911>>>>>>>        // Now is the time to setup our driver default values by reading the driver .int file:
89911>>>>>>>        Send SetupDriverDefaults SQLConnection.sDriverID
89912>>>>>>>        
89912>>>>>>>    End_Procedure                 
89913>>>>>>>    
89913>>>>>>>    // Similar to _SqlCheckCurrentDriver but generates no error and it doesn't 
89913>>>>>>>    // attempt to load the driver.
89913>>>>>>>    // Returns true if the passed driver is SQL based.        
89913>>>>>>>    Function IsSQLDriver String sDriverID Returns Boolean
89915>>>>>>>        Boolean bOK                         
89915>>>>>>>        Integer iDriver
89915>>>>>>>        
89915>>>>>>>        Get IsDAWSQLDriver sDriverID to bOK
89916>>>>>>>
89916>>>>>>>        If (bOK = False) Begin
89918>>>>>>>            Get IsMertechDriver sDriverID to bOK
89919>>>>>>>        End                                     
89919>>>>>>>>
89919>>>>>>>
89919>>>>>>>        Function_Return bOK
89920>>>>>>>    End_Function
89921>>>>>>>            
89921>>>>>>>    // Reads the driver .int file and sets class properties of the cDbUpdateFunctionLibrary accordingly.
89921>>>>>>>    Procedure SetupDriverDefaults String sDriverID
89923>>>>>>>        String sAttributeValue                                               
89923>>>>>>>        Integer iDriverID
89923>>>>>>>        Boolean bNULL bSQLDriver
89923>>>>>>>        
89923>>>>>>>        Get IsSQLDriver sDriverID to bSQLDriver
89924>>>>>>>        If (bSQLDriver = False) Begin
89926>>>>>>>            Procedure_Return
89927>>>>>>>        End
89927>>>>>>>>
89927>>>>>>>            
89927>>>>>>>        Get DriverIndex sDriverID to iDriverID
89928>>>>>>>        
89928>>>>>>>        // Driver default values for various data types:
89928>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_ASCII of iDriverID      to sAttributeValue
89931>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueASCII                                   to sAttributeValue
89932>>>>>>>
89932>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_BINARY of iDriverID     to sAttributeValue
89935>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueBinary                                  to sAttributeValue
89936>>>>>>>
89936>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_DATE of iDriverID       to sAttributeValue
89939>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueDate                                    to sAttributeValue
89940>>>>>>>
89940>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_DATETIME of iDriverID   to sAttributeValue
89943>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueDateTime                                to sAttributeValue
89944>>>>>>>
89944>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_NUMERIC of iDriverID    to sAttributeValue
89947>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueNumeric                                 to sAttributeValue
89948>>>>>>>
89948>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_TEXT of iDriverID       to sAttributeValue
89951>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueText                                    to sAttributeValue
89952>>>>>>>        
89952>>>>>>>        // The default setting for the "nullability" of newly created ASCII columns.
89952>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_ASCII      of iDriverID to bNULL
89955>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableASCII to bNULL
89956>>>>>>>        
89956>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_BINARY     of iDriverID to bNULL
89959>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableBinary to bNULL
89960>>>>>>>        
89960>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_DATE       of iDriverID to bNULL
89963>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableDate to bNULL
89964>>>>>>>        
89964>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_DATETIME   of iDriverID to bNULL
89967>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableDateTime to bNULL
89968>>>>>>>        
89968>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_NUMERIC    of iDriverID to bNULL
89971>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableNumeric to bNULL
89972>>>>>>>        
89972>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_TEXT       of iDriverID to bNULL
89975>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableText to bNULL
89976>>>>>>>        
89976>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
89977>>>>>>>    
89977>>>>>>>    Function SQLLogin tSQLConnection SQLConnection Returns Boolean
89979>>>>>>>        Boolean bOK bIsDaw bIsMertech bTrusted 
89979>>>>>>>        String sConnectionString sServer sDatabase sUserId sPassword sDriverID sCheck
89979>>>>>>>        Handle hoErrorObj hoDriver hoIniFile 
89979>>>>>>>        Integer iDriverID
89979>>>>>>>        
89979>>>>>>>        Move False to bOK
89980>>>>>>>        
89980>>>>>>>        Get IsDAWSQLDriver SQLConnection.sDriverID to bIsDaw
89981>>>>>>>        If (bIsDaw = False) Begin
89983>>>>>>>            Get IsMertechDriver SQLConnection.sDriverID to bIsMertech
89984>>>>>>>            If (bIsMertech = False) Begin
89986>>>>>>>                Function_Return False
89987>>>>>>>            End
89987>>>>>>>>
89987>>>>>>>        End  
89987>>>>>>>>
89987>>>>>>>        
89987>>>>>>>        Move Error_Object_Id to hoErrorObj
89988>>>>>>>        Move Self to Error_Object_Id        
89989>>>>>>>        
89989>>>>>>>        Get phoSQLConnectionIniFile to hoIniFile
89990>>>>>>>        Get ConstructConnectionString SQLConnection.sDriverID SQLConnection.sServer SQLConnection.sDatabase SQLConnection.bTrusted SQLConnection.sUserID SQLConnection.sPassword to sConnectionString
89991>>>>>>>        Get DriverIndex SQLConnection.sDriverID to iDriverID
89992>>>>>>>        If (iDriverID = 0) Begin
89994>>>>>>>            Move hoErrorObj to Error_Object_Id
89995>>>>>>>            Function_Return False
89996>>>>>>>        End
89996>>>>>>>>
89996>>>>>>>        
89996>>>>>>>        // There's a bug in Mertech drivers creating "an Exception error" in the debugger (probably will crash an application too.)
89996>>>>>>>        If (bIsMertech = False) Begin
89998>>>>>>>            Set_Attribute DF_DRIVER_SILENT_LOGIN of iDriverID to SQLConnection.bSilentLogin
90001>>>>>>>        End
90001>>>>>>>>
90001>>>>>>>        
90001>>>>>>>        Get Create (RefClass(cDbUpdateDatabaseDriver)) to hoDriver
90002>>>>>>>        Set psDriverID of hoDriver to SQLConnection.sDriverID
90003>>>>>>>        Get DbLogin    of hoDriver sConnectionString SQLConnection.sServer SQLConnection.sDatabase SQLConnection.bTrusted SQLConnection.sUserID SQLConnection.sPassword to bOK
90004>>>>>>>        Send Destroy   of hoDriver
90005>>>>>>>        Move hoErrorObj to Error_Object_Id
90006>>>>>>>        
90006>>>>>>>        Function_Return bOK
90007>>>>>>>    End_Function
90008>>>>>>>    
