92814>>>>>    // Checks if the passed Table;
92814>>>>>    // 1) Already has a Filelist entry that points to SQL and
92814>>>>>    // 2) It has an .int file. 
92814>>>>>    // If both is True it should already be connected to SQL
92814>>>>>    Function SQLUtilTableIsAttached String sDriverID Handle hTable Returns Boolean
92816>>>>>        Boolean bExists bRootName
92816>>>>>        String sRootName sDataPath
92816>>>>>        Integer iCount
92816>>>>>        
92816>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_ROOT_NAME of hTable to sRootName
92819>>>>>        Move (sRootName contains sDriverID) to bRootName
92820>>>>>        
92820>>>>>        Get psDataPathFirstPart to sDataPath
92821>>>>>        Get vFolderExists sDataPath to bExists
92822>>>>>        If (bExists = False) Begin
92824>>>>>            // If the path doesn't exist it cannot have an .int file and we're done, although it shouldn't happen.
92824>>>>>            Function_Return False
92825>>>>>        End                      
92825>>>>>>
92825>>>>>        
92825>>>>>        Get vFolderFormat sDataPath to sDataPath         
92826>>>>>        Get _TableNameOnly sRootName to sRootName
92827>>>>>        Get vFilePathExists (sDataPath + sRootName + ".int") to bExists
92828>>>>>
92828>>>>>        Function_Return (bRootName = True and bExists = True)
92829>>>>>    End_Function       
