93329>>>>>    // SQL column names can be case-sensitive. This function is used to check that
93329>>>>>    // the passed sFieldName has the correct spelling.                            
93329>>>>>    // Used with Embedded SQL statement calls.
93329>>>>>    // If the spelling or fieldname doesn't exist, the return value is "" (blank).
93329>>>>>    Function _SqlFindColumnName String sTableName String sColumnName Returns String
93331>>>>>        String sRetval sValue sConnectionString sDriverID 
93331>>>>>        String[] sColumnNamesArray
93332>>>>>        Integer iCount iColumns
93332>>>>>
93332>>>>>        Move "" to sRetval
93333>>>>>        Get psDriverID to sDriverID
93334>>>>>        Get SqlUtilEnumerateColumns sDriverID sTableName to sColumnNamesArray
93335>>>>>        Move (SizeOfArray(sColumnNamesArray)) to iColumns
93336>>>>>        Decrement iColumns
93337>>>>>        
93337>>>>>        For iCount from 0 to iColumns
93343>>>>>>
93343>>>>>            Move sColumnNamesArray[iCount] to sValue
93344>>>>>            If (Uppercase(sColumnName) = Uppercase(sValue)) Begin
93346>>>>>                Move sValue to sRetval
93347>>>>>                Move iColumns to iCount // We're done.
93348>>>>>            End
93348>>>>>>
93348>>>>>        Loop                           
93349>>>>>>
93349>>>>>        
93349>>>>>        Function_Return sRetval
93350>>>>>    End_Function
