95508>>>>>    
95508>>>>>    // Returns True if the passed hTable (filelist slot number) is an Alias table.
95508>>>>>    // An Alias file/table is a filelist number that share the same Physical filename
95508>>>>>    // but which Logical name is different.
95508>>>>>    // Note: If the table cannot be opened; the table is not considered to be an Alias.
95508>>>>>    Function UtilTableIsAlias Handle hTable Returns Boolean
95510>>>>>        String sPhysicalName sPhysicalNameCompare     
95510>>>>>        Boolean bOpened bOK
95510>>>>>        
95510>>>>>        Open hTable
95512>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_OPENED of hTable to bOpened
95515>>>>>        If (bOpened = False) Begin
95517>>>>>            Function_Return False
95518>>>>>        End                      
95518>>>>>>
95518>>>>>        
95518>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_PHYSICAL_NAME of hTable to sPhysicalName 
95521>>>>>        Get _TableNameOnly sPhysicalName to sPhysicalName
95522>>>>>        Close hTable
95523>>>>>        
95523>>>>>        Move 0 to hTable
95524>>>>>        Repeat
95524>>>>>>
95524>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_FILE_NEXT_USED of hTable to hTable
95527>>>>>            If (hTable > 0) Begin         
95529>>>>>                Open hTable
95531>>>>>                Get_Attribute DF_FILE_OPENED of hTable to bOpened
95534>>>>>                If (bOpened = True) Begin
95536>>>>>                    Get_Attribute DF_FILE_PHYSICAL_NAME of hTable to sPhysicalNameCompare 
95539>>>>>                    Close hTable
95540>>>>>                    Get _TableNameOnly sPhysicalNameCompare to sPhysicalNameCompare
95541>>>>>                    If (Uppercase(sPhysicalName) = Uppercase(sPhysicalNameCompare)) Begin
95543>>>>>                        Function_Return True
95544>>>>>                    End
95544>>>>>>
95544>>>>>                End
95544>>>>>>
95544>>>>>            End
95544>>>>>>
95544>>>>>        Until (hTable = 0)
95546>>>>>        
95546>>>>>        Function_Return False
95547>>>>>    End_Function
95548>>>>>    
95548>>>>>    // To Open a table with any driver.
95548>>>>>    // Note: If the driver is <> DATAFLEX_ID  - login credentials are used; it is then assumed 
95548>>>>>    //       that the proper login properties has been setup properly with the cSQLConnections object.
95548>>>>>    //
95548>>>>>    // If the open command fails the Err flag will be reset to false, at the end of the function!
95548>>>>>    // The found flag is still used to indicate if the open was successful or not. The function
95548>>>>>    // returns a True if successful (table could be opened).
95548>>>>>    //
95548>>>>>    // Using the "Open As" syntax with drivers means that we don't need to rely on .int file settings.
95548>>>>>    // This is good because with DFConnectionID's those credentials doesn't need to be available in
95548>>>>>    // the .int file (and probably aren't). As long as the login properties of this object have been
95548>>>>>    // set properly we can open the table.
95548>>>>>    //
95548>>>>>    // DAW Driver Syntax:
95548>>>>>    //  <CKId>:<Schema>#<Table>@<ConnectString>|<Filename>.int
95548>>>>>    //  Now the @<ConnectString> can be followed by a pipe character '|' followed by the name of the INT file.
95548>>>>>    //  Doing so, the driver will apply the information from the .INT file to the passed direct Open String.
95548>>>>>    //  Note that when an INT file has been passed, it will skip the keyword DRIVER_NAME, SERVER_NAME,
95548>>>>>    //  DATABASE_NAME and SCHEMA_NAME from the INT file because those are supposed to be supplied in the String already. 
95548>>>>>    //  Open mode; iMode = DF_SHARE or DF_EXCLUSIVE.
95548>>>>>    //
95548>>>>>    // DAW Driver Sample:
95548>>>>>    //   Open "MSSQLDRV:dbo#MyFile@SERVER=(local)\SQLEXPRESS;Trusted_Connection=yes;DATABASE=OrderEntry|options|intfile=MyFile.int"
95548>>>>>    //
95548>>>>>    // Mertech Driver Samples:
95548>>>>>    //   SQLFlex:   Open "sql_drv:\\<serverName>\<database>*<owner>*<tableName>=<numberFieds>" as table 
95548>>>>>    //   MySQLFlex: Open "mdsmysql:\\<serverName>\<database>*<tableName>=<numberFieds>" as table 
95548>>>>>    //   PgFlex:    Open "mdspgsql:\\<serverName>\<database>*<schema>*<tableName>=<numberFieds>" as table 
95548>>>>>    //   ORAFlex:   Open "ora_drv:\\<serverName>\<owner>*<tableName>=<numberFieds>" as table 
95548>>>>>    Function UtilTableOpen Integer hTable String sTableName Integer iMode Returns Boolean
